-- New Zealand Beats Host England in Cricket Series With Rain Out
-- B y   C h r i s t o p h e r   E l s e r
-- 2013-06-27T22:18:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-27/new-zealand-beats-host-england-in-cricket-series-with-rain-out.html
New Zealand beat  England  1-0 in
their Twenty20 cricket series after tonight’s match was rained
out at the Oval in  London  after two balls.  New Zealand won the toss and put England in to bat in the
match, which was delayed by rain. Opening batsman Michael Lumb
was out for 2, caught off the bowling of Mitchell McClenaghan.
Alex Hales hadn’t yet scored when play was stopped. It was
abandoned shortly after 9 p.m. local time, giving New Zealand
the victory after it won the first match by 5 runs.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christopher Elser at 
 celser@bloomberg.net  